        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-18T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-18T05:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/11–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-18T18:00:00+08:00">November 18, 1948—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 18—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2467. Civil Air Transport, CAT, has requested permission operate evacuation
                    shuttle Shanghai–Nanking–Hong Kong and has received verbal assurances permission
                    will be granted.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, pouched Nanking 1865.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
